  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The pathophysiology of acute ischemic pain is not well established. The aim of the present
      study was to investigate acute ischemic pain in humans with a view to establish a scientific
      model to perform future studies. The investigators examined whether peripheral nerve damage
      and acute inflammation occur during short episodes of acute ischemia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
